cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper focuses on the maximum achievable rate of a full-duplex relay system, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies a filter-and-forward relay system, which is a common technique in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the joint optimization of transmit power allocation and frequency response of the filter, which is a problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with a full-duplex relay system in frequency-selective channels, which is a topic in communication and networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the relay system in terms of achievable rate, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates.
